race.comment: THINK LIKE PADDY (1) resumes here but got up to Group 3 level when last in work and has tuned up for this with two easy trials. Gets the reliable Dunn/Mallyon combination and can run a big race while fresh. BLUE ALLURE (10) is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and will be rock-hard fit for this. In the right race and is a winning hope. CARPACCIO (7) is first-up but has a solid fresh record and is more than capable enough on his day. Top-three aspirations. SMART RECOGNITION (2) has won over this course and distance and gets 3kg weight relief with the claim. Shapes as a key runner. DETRIMENTAL (3) strips fitter second-up from the spell and maps ideally from gate two. In the mix.
